                        <msContents>
                            <textLang mainLang="la"/>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="1r" to="180v" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Psalter</title>
                                <incipit defective="true">ego custodiui uias duras</incipit>
                                <explicit defective="true">et reuertetur in terram suam in illa die</explicit>
                                <note>
                                    <p>The first part of the text of the psalter is missing; it begins in the middle of Psalm 16:4. The fragment found by former librarian <persName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/person/102623">Oscar Wieselgren</persName> in <date when="1919"/> in the <orgName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/org/100007">Royal Danish Library</orgName> (Fragm. 3136; <locus from="Photocopy_1r" to="Photocopy_1v" scheme="folios"/>) bears the text and gloss of Psalm 9:7–18.</p>
                                    <p>Two leaves have been torn out between <locus from="180" to="180" scheme="folios"/> and <locus from="181" to="181" scheme="folios"/> resulting in loss of text; the psalter thus ends in the middle of Psalm 145:4.</p>
                                </note>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="1r" to="180v" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Gloss</title>
                                <incipit>uel uias latronis id est quia latro merito ego pacior imerito</incipit>
                                <explicit>Prius corda mundat ut post salutaria infundat</explicit>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="181r" to="191v" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">The Catholic Canticles with gloss</title>
                                <msItem>
                                    <locus from="181r" to="181v" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <title type="desc">Canticle of Isaias the Prophet (Isa. 12:1-6)</title>
                                </msItem>
                                <msItem>
                                    <locus from="181v" to="182v" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <title type="desc">Canticle of Ezechias (Isa. 38:10–20)</title>
                                    <rubric>scriptura ezechie regis iuda</rubric>
                                </msItem>
                                <msItem>
                                    <locus from="182v" to="183v" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <title type="desc">Canticle of Anna (1 Sam. 2:1–10)</title>
                                    <note>
                                        <quote>CANTICVM ANNAE</quote> added in margin.</note>
                                </msItem>
                                <msItem>
                                    <locus from="184r" to="185v" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <title type="desc">Canticle of Moses (Exod. 15:1–19)</title>
                                </msItem>
                                <msItem>
                                    <locus from="185v" to="187v" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <title type="desc">Canticle of Habacuc (Hab. 3:2–19)</title>
                                    <note>
                                        <quote>ORATIO ABACVC PRO IGNORATIONIBVS</quote> added in margin.</note>
                                </msItem>
                                <msItem>
                                    <locus from="187v" to="191v" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <title type="desc">Canticle of Moses (Deut. 32:1-43)</title>
                                    <rubric>Canticum Moysi hominis dei</rubric>
                                    <note>Due to leaves missing, the canticle ends at Deut. 32:40.</note>
                                </msItem>
                            </msItem>
                        </msContents>
                        <physDesc>
                            <objectDesc>
                                <supportDesc material="parchment">
                                    <support>
                                        <p>
                                            <locus from="1" to="191" scheme="folios"/>
                                            <material>Parchment</material>
                                            <dimensions type="leaf">
                                                <height quantity="255" unit="mm"/>
                                                <width quantity="170" unit="mm"/>
                                            </dimensions>
                                        </p>
                                    </support>
                                    <extent>
                                        <measure type="textblockLeaves" quantity="191" unit="folios"/>
                                    </extent>
                                    <condition>The manuscript shows clear signs of use, with dirt around the lower corners and edges. Some holes and tears, some with remnants of stitching (e.g. <locus from="109" to="109" scheme="folios"/>); spillage stains at <locus from="179" to="179" scheme="folios"/>. At the bottom of <locus from="38" to="38" scheme="folios"/>, the ruling has caused the parchment to split.</condition>
                                </supportDesc>
                                <layoutDesc>
                                    <layout columns="3">
                                        <note>
                                            <p>The manuscipt has the customary layout of an early 12th century glossed book of the Bible (see <bibl>
                                                    <title ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107318">De Hamel</title>
                                                    <citedRange from="14" to="15" unit="page"/>
                                                </bibl>), with a central column for the Bible text (60 mm), and two surrounding columns for the glosses (outer column 45-50 mm; inner column 35-45 mm). <locus from="1r" to="96v" scheme="folios"/>, blind ruling of central column, 18 lines per column, pricking intermittently visible; <locus from="97r" to="191v" scheme="folios"/> 16 lines per central column. From <locus from="76r" to="89r" scheme="folios"/> and <locus from="97r" to="191v" scheme="folios"/> the ruling extends to the spaces intended for the gloss, i.e. the inner and outer columns - and in some cases also the upper margin (e.g. <locus from="79r" to="79r" scheme="folios"/>) as well as a few lines below the bottom line of the central column - at a height of two lines of commentary for each line of Bible text. From <locus from="161r" to="191v" scheme="folios"/>, ruling of the spaces intended for the gloss is intermittent.</p>
                                            <p/>
                                        </note>
                                    </layout>
                                </layoutDesc>
                            </objectDesc>
                            <handDesc>
                                <p/>
                                <handNote xml:id="hand-1">
                                    <locus from="1r" to="128v" scheme="folios"/>Pregothic.</handNote>
                                <handNote xml:id="hand-2">
                                    <locus from="128v" to="132v" scheme="folios"/>Pregothic.</handNote>
                                <handNote xml:id="hand-3">
                                    <locus from="133r" to="173r" scheme="folios"/>Pregothic.</handNote>
                                <handNote xml:id="hand-4">
                                    <locus from="173r" to="186v" scheme="folios"/>Pregothic.</handNote>
                                <handNote xml:id="hand-5">
                                    <locus from="187r" to="189v" scheme="folios"/>Pregothic.</handNote>
                                <handNote xml:id="hand-6">
                                    <locus from="190r" to="191v" scheme="folios"/>Pregothic. (possibly same as Hand 5).</handNote>
                            </handDesc>
                            <additions>
                                <p>
                                    <locus from="1r" to="1r" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <note>Top left corner in brown ink: <quote>CXXI</quote>; below, in pencil: <quote>Ps. 16, 4</quote>; bottom centre, in brown ink in Jaches's hand: <quote>226 Nov. Num</quote>; the signum is found again on <locus from="9r" to="9r" scheme="folios"/>.</note>
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    <locus from="1r" to="191v" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <note>Various annotations (e.g. <locus from="27r" to="27r" scheme="folios"/>, <locus from="47r" to="47r" scheme="folios"/>, <locus from="63v" to="63v" scheme="folios"/>, <locus from="84v" to="84v" scheme="folios"/>, <locus from="160r" to="160r" scheme="folios"/>), doodles (e.g. <locus from="45r" to="45r" scheme="folios"/>, <locus from="52r" to="52r" scheme="folios"/>, <locus from="55r" to="55r" scheme="folios"/>, <locus from="56r" to="56r" scheme="folios"/>, <locus from="183r" to="183r" scheme="folios"/>), and corrections (e.g. <locus from="160r" to="160r" scheme="folios"/>, <locus from="72r" to="72r" scheme="folios"/>, <locus from="191r" to="191r" scheme="folios"/>) in different medieval hands throughout the manuscript.</note>
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    <locus from="2r" to="2r" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <note>Mid-outer margin, in pencil by a modern hand: <quote>Ps. 17.</quote>.</note>
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    <locus from="2r" to="149r" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <note>Psalm numbers according to the Hebrew numbering in light brown ink by a medieval hand. At Psalm 118, the sections headed by the Hebrew letters Beth and Gimel are numbered as xx and xxi; after this, this numbering ceases.</note>
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    <locus from="191v" to="191v" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <note>Alphabet in red in in near-contemporary hand in margin.</note>
                                </p>
                            </additions>
                            <decoDesc>
                                <p> Main text in black or brown ink; rubrics in red.</p>
                                <p> First word up to entire first line of psalm in display script.</p>
                                <p>
                                    <!--The initials display three types of patterns: the first corresponds to quires 1-10, the second to quires 11-16 and 18-24 (or 25), and the third to quires 17 and the last two folios. Where initials have been missed, they are filled in brown or black ink (e.g. 11v)-->
                                </p>
                                <decoNote type="initials">
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="2r" to="77r" scheme="folios"/>: plain psalm initials over 2 lines in a repeating pattern of one blue with red flourishing, one red, and one green.</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="1r" to="80v" scheme="folios"/>: plain verse initials over 1 line alternating between red, green, and blue.</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="79r" to="131v" scheme="folios"/>, <locus from="141v" to="189v" scheme="folios"/>: plain psalm initials over 2 lines alternating between one blue with red flourishing and one red. The initial <quote>D</quote> on <locus from="166r" to="166r" scheme="folios"/> has a different style and colour scheme.</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="81r" to="133r" scheme="folios"/>, <locus from="141r" to="189v" scheme="folios"/>: plain verse initials over 1 line alternating between red and blue.</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="135r" to="139r" scheme="folios"/>: two plain red and one plain green psalm initial over 2 lines.</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="133v" to="140v" scheme="folios"/>, <locus from="190r" to="191v" scheme="folios"/>: plain verse initials over 1 line in red.</p>
                                </decoNote>
                            </decoDesc>
